channel.description:
Hi everyone ! :wave:

I am trying to use the [standard Woo API](https://woocommerce.github.io/woocommerce-rest-api-docs) in Frontity.
I realize that the [Custom Post Type in Frontity](https://docs.frontity.org/api-reference-1/wordpress-source#state-source-posttypes) (product in WC) require of type "type" field fixed to "product" and the "link" field must be included in the response.
both things can be done using the following snippet:

    function pxe_wc_rest_prepare_product( $response, $post ) {
        $response->data['type'] = 'product';
        $response->data['link'] = get_permalink( $post->id );

        return $response;
    }
    add_filter( 'woocommerce_rest_prepare_product_object', 'pxe_wc_rest_prepare_product', 10, 2 );

Is there anything else that should be included in the response?
